00:45:43.050 --> 00:45:47.530
through all of that as well, but
because of the dispersed leadership

00:45:47.530 --> 00:45:51.200
in that period, when there was
a lot of regional infighting,

00:45:51.200 --> 00:45:56.590
you didn't have this iconic,
central power of the --

00:45:56.590 --> 00:46:00.960
of a Solomonic emperor during
that brief period until 1855

00:46:00.960 --> 00:46:03.720
when it was re-galvanized
under Tewodros.

00:46:03.720 --> 00:46:07.610
But you're right in suggesting

00:46:07.610 --> 00:46:14.430
that Emperor Haile Selassie not
only was the only viable choice

00:46:14.430 --> 00:46:17.250
to lead the country
when he was chosen as --

00:46:17.250 --> 00:46:21.590
first as Region and then
[foreign name] and later

00:46:21.590 --> 00:46:25.010
as Emperor [foreign
name], I guess in 1930.

00:46:25.010 --> 00:46:30.640
He was outstandingly visionary
from a global perspective.

00:46:30.640 --> 00:46:35.820
He was, as you say, progressive
in the best sense of the word

00:46:35.820 --> 00:46:40.430
in that he wanted excellence
and education,

00:46:40.430 --> 00:46:44.370
and he did so without a
foundation of great wealth.

00:46:44.370 --> 00:46:47.460
So, he actually introduced
modern education.

00:46:47.460 --> 00:46:50.890 position:56%
He introduced modern infrastructure,
technology, and so on.

00:46:50.890 --> 00:46:52.190
He was enlightened.

00:46:52.190 --> 00:46:55.110
And it was no accident that,
and I didn't mention it in this,

00:46:55.110 --> 00:47:01.420
but no accident that he was highly
engaged in the [inaudible] Movement

00:47:01.420 --> 00:47:05.530
because he was looking for
bridges between the world.

00:47:05.530 --> 00:47:06.830
Here was the irony.

00:47:06.830 --> 00:47:09.400
He was heavily involved in
creating the [inaudible] Movement

00:47:09.400 --> 00:47:13.340
and sustaining that, at the same
time as he exhibited a belief

00:47:13.340 --> 00:47:16.350
in collective security, which
is why he committed so strongly

00:47:16.350 --> 00:47:17.710
to the United Nations,

00:47:17.710 --> 00:47:20.660
and the United Nations
mission in Korea, for example.

00:47:20.660 --> 00:47:25.690
He -- in fact, the
revolution against him,

00:47:25.690 --> 00:47:26.990
or the coup against him rather,

00:47:26.990 --> 00:47:31.240
and the [inaudible] revolutionary
thought which was introduced later

00:47:31.240 --> 00:47:36.990
by the Derg, was absolutely
regressive in, to my mind,

00:47:36.990 --> 00:47:45.570 position:56%
in the sense that it was an attempt
to stop some of this broad, liberal,

00:47:45.570 --> 00:47:47.470
democratic ideals,
which the emperor had.

00:47:47.470 --> 00:47:52.840
I mean, he was clearly a proponent
of a constitutional monarchy

00:47:52.840 --> 00:47:57.200
and a stable democratically
elected government,

00:47:57.200 --> 00:48:02.210
and had he been given the time,
I think we'd have seen Ethiopia,

00:48:02.210 --> 00:48:08.090
not only have stable democratic
institutions to this day, but also,

00:48:08.090 --> 00:48:11.790
great economic benefits
as a result of that,

00:48:11.790 --> 00:48:18.790
without compromising Ethiopia's
sense of its unique identity.

00:48:20.310 --> 00:48:26.510
So, does that address
